1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:04,102
Deep in frigid oceans, a colossal marvel exists.

2
00:00:04,052 --> 00:00:08,467
The Lion's Mane Jellyfish, the longest creature on our planet.

3
00:00:08,467 --> 00:00:11,807
Its immense size truly defies imagination.

4
00:00:11,807 --> 00:00:14,510
Its bell can reach eight feet across.

5
00:00:14,510 --> 00:00:18,812
But the true spectacle lies in its thousands of trailing tentacles.

6
00:00:18,812 --> 00:00:23,052
These delicate, ribbon-like strands stretch to astonishing lengths.

7
00:00:23,052 --> 00:00:27,267
Imagine something longer than a blue whale or a skyscraper.

8
00:00:27,267 --> 00:00:30,657
Some specimens exceed 120 feet.

9
00:00:30,657 --> 00:00:35,297
Truly the planet's extended giant, a living, moving leviathan.

10
00:00:35,297 --> 00:00:41,300
This magnificent predator prefers icy, dark waters of the Arctic and North Atlantic.

11
00:00:41,300 --> 00:00:46,040
It drifts silently, a ghostly presence in the deep, patiently waiting.

12
00:00:46,040 --> 00:00:50,555
Its thousands of fine tentacles are armed with powerful stinging cells.

13
00:00:50,555 --> 00:00:56,607
These venomous threads entangle small fish and plankton, paralyzing them instantly for consumption.

14
00:00:56,607 --> 00:01:01,672
Despite its fearsome size and potent sting, encounters with humans are rare.

15
00:01:01,672 --> 00:01:08,360
This elusive deep-sea inhabitant remains one of the ocean's most breathtaking, mysterious wonders.

